<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; color:#000000; bEditID:r3st1; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<font face="Arial, sans-serif" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;">Hey Grads!</font><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><span style="background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);"><font face="arial"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">Remember&nbsp;</span></font>learning<font face="arial"><span style="font-size: 12pt;">&nbsp;about the power of your political voice during the Bite The Ballot session on NCS?</span></font></span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255);">&nbsp; Well now is your chance to #TakePower. Join the BtB team and become an accredited Changemaker and we will help you organise events and get involved in national movements such as National Voter Registration Drive (NVRD).</span></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><div style="font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 16px;"><font face="Arial, sans-serif">We'll be bringing all of you together talk about how you can become a BtB changemakers and contribute to British Politics. &nbsp;If you wish to take part or are returning after the first session, you have a choice of two days and locations, to make it easier for you to attend - click the relevant link below to get your free Eventbrite ticket (make sure you only sign up to one!):</font></div><div style="font-size: 16px;"><ul style="font-family: arial;"><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><a href="https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/bite-the-ballot-changemakers-session-2-thursday-tickets-20421823223"><font color="#cc0000"><b>Thursday 14th January in Waterloo</b></font></a>&nbsp;(Elizabeth House, 39 York Road, London, SE1 &amp;NQ)</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><a href="https://www.eventbrite.co.uk/e/bite-the-ballot-changemakers-session-2-friday-tickets-20422203360"><font color="#cc0000"><b>Friday 15th January in Kentish Town</b></font></a>&nbsp;(Highgate Studios, 53-79 Highgate Road, London, NW5 1TL)</font></li></ul><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif;">If you can't attend either, please email graduates@the-challenge.org. If you would like any more information please read below.</span></div></div><div style="font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt;"><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div><div><b><font face="Arial, sans-serif">What does it involve?</font></b></div><div><b><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></b></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Changemakers will participate in three main activities between February and May 2016:</font></div><div><ul><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><b>Participation:&nbsp;</b>Help BTB with their National Voter Registration Drive in early February.</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><b>Online and Offline Social Action:&nbsp;</b>Bring your local communities together to talk about the big issues.</font></li><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><b>Accountability and Decision Making:&nbsp;</b>Organise and take part in your local 'Leaders Live' event, getting the chance to question and hold to account the people who make the big decisions where you live.</font></li></ul><div><b><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Why should I take part?</font></b></div></div><div><b><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></b></div><div><ul><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">You'll become an accredited Changemaker, with the opportunity to train future generations of young people on everything you've learned.</font></li></ul></div><div><ul><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">You'll learn loads of new skills, including campaign planning, effective social media, political advocacy, fundraising, and so many more!</font></li></ul></div><div><ul><li><font face="Arial, sans-serif">You'll get VIP access to a range of future opportunities with BTB, including travel, international training and employment.</font></li></ul></div></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Our first BtB session consisted of ideas for how you would engage a community you care about for National Voter Registration Drive (NVRD) from February 1st - 7th. At the end of the session, everyone was called to action to:</font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">a) Register to vote: see&nbsp;<a href="http://bitetheballot.co.uk/home/register/">here</a>&nbsp;for more information about registering to vote, and&nbsp;<a href="https://www.gov.uk/register-to-vote">here</a>&nbsp;to register</font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">b) Make your NVRD ideas come to life and help us make history this February</font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">Bite the Ballot and The Challenge are going to make history this February. We invite you to be there.</font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif"><br></font></div><div><font face="Arial, sans-serif">#TakePower</font></div></div><div style="font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt;"><br></div><div style="font-family: arial; color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: 12pt;"><img src="https://c.na8.content.force.com/servlet/servlet.ImageServer?id=015C0000002r6Mi&amp;oid=00D80000000ZK1f" border="0" align="left" alt=""></div></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-family: arial; font-size: 12pt;"><br></div>]]></td>
